Commuters have complained about constant delays and the matter has now been discussed in the provincial legislature. CAPE TOWN - Metrorail's constant woes and failure to properly communicate with commuters have come under scrutiny in the Western Cape Legislature.Problems at the rail operator have mounted over the last fortnight after at least two trains were set alight in Cape Town.Commuters have complained about constant delays and the matter has now been discussed in the provincial legislature.Democratic Alliance MPL Ricardo Mackenzie says the problems with Metrorail are affecting the province's economy. Over 700,000 people make use of the public train service on a daily basis in the Western Cape, representing a substantial chunk of our population which contributes to our economy. &quot;Consistent train delays and disruptions are direct results of incessant failure at Metrorail in the Western Cape and continue to hamper the lives of these residents. 